The paper deals with the problem of distribution testing using locally differentially private mechanisms, which involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The focus is on discrete distributions, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also proposes a new mechanism called RAPTOR, which involves randomized algorithms and probability theory (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with sample complexity and optimality, which is a common theme in statistical learning theory (cs.SI).
